# Paws & Stay

## Project Description

Paws & Stay is a full-stack web application designed to connect pet owners with trusted pet sitters.  
The platform allows users to register pets, book sitting sessions, and manage pet care activities in an organized and user-friendly system.

This project demonstrates the integration of a Flask backend API with a React frontend, implementing full CRUD functionality, user-pet relationships, and booking management.

---

## Project Team

This project was collaboratively developed by the following team members:

- Sharon Njoroge 
- Sumeya Hirsi 
- Fredrick Rangara  
- Marvin Kioko 
- Carl Kiprono  

Each member contributed to a specific core feature of the application to ensure smooth collaboration and clean code structure.

---

## Technologies Used

### Frontend
- React.js  
- JavaScript  
- HTML  
- CSS  
- React Router  
- Formik & Yup for form validation  
- Fetch API  

### Backend
- Python  
- Flask  
- Flask-RESTful  
- SQLAlchemy  
- SQLite Database  
- Flask-Migrate  

### Tools
- Git and GitHub  
- Postman  
- Visual Studio Code  

---

## Features

Users of the system can:

- Register pets  
- View all available pets  
- Book pet sitting sessions  
- Edit pet details  
- Delete pets  
- View pets they own  
- View pets they are sitting for  

